### Test OTP-based Password Reset Endpoints

### 1. Request Password Reset OTP
POST http://localhost:5000/api/Auth/forgot-password
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "test@example.com"
}

###

### 2. Verify Invalid OTP (should fail)
POST http://localhost:5000/api/Auth/verify-reset-otp
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "test@example.com",
  "otp": "000000"
}

###

### 3. Reset Password with Invalid Token (should fail)
POST http://localhost:5000/api/Auth/reset-password-otp
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "test@example.com",
  "resetToken": "invalid-token",
  "newPassword": "NewPassword123!",
  "confirmPassword": "NewPassword123!"
}

###

### 4. Test Validation - Empty Email
POST http://localhost:5000/api/Auth/forgot-password
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": ""
}

###

### 5. Test Validation - Invalid Email Format
POST http://localhost:5000/api/Auth/forgot-password
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "invalid-email"
}

###